\begin{abstract}
This paper reformulates Quantum Information Gravity (QIG) using category theory. We define objects and morphisms corresponding to quantum informational states and entropic transformations, and demonstrate how QIG dynamics emerge as functorial mappings on the category of informational geometries.
\end{abstract}

\section{Category of Information States}

Let $\mathcal{C}$ be a category where:
\begin{itemize}
  \item Objects: Entropic manifolds $(M, \Omega)$, where $M$ is a topological space and $\Omega$ is a quantum information density field.
  \item Morphisms: Entropy-preserving maps $f : (M, \Omega) \to (N, \Omega')$ such that $S = k \ln \Omega$ is invariant under $f$.
\end{itemize}

\section{Information Functor and Curvature}

Define a functor $\mathcal{F} : \mathcal{C} \to \mathsf{Geo}$ mapping entropic states to differential geometric manifolds with entropy-modulated metrics:
\[
\mathcal{F}(M, \Omega) = (M, \tilde{g}_{\mu\nu} = f(S) g_{\mu\nu})
\]

\section{Natural Transformations and QIG Dynamics}

Let $\mathcal{T} : \mathcal{F}_1 \Rightarrow \mathcal{F}_2$ be a natural transformation between functors describing different scaling regimes (e.g., classical vs. quantum gravity).

Each component $\mathcal{T}_{(M,\Omega)}$ modifies metric scaling functions:
\[
\mathcal{T}_{(M,\Omega)} : f_1(S) \mapsto f_2(S)
\]

\section{Commutative Diagrams and Conservation Laws}

For entropy-conserving dynamics, the following diagram commutes:
\[
\begin{array}{ccc}
(M,\Omega) & \xrightarrow{f} & (N,\Omega') \\
\downarrow \mathcal{F} &  & \downarrow \mathcal{F} \\
(M, \tilde{g}) & \xrightarrow{\mathcal{F}(f)} & (N, \tilde{g}')
\end{array}
\]

This enforces curvature consistency across informational transitions.

\section{Conclusion}

The categorical reformulation of QIG reveals its structural coherence: entropic geometries form a category, and gravitational emergence is encoded as a functorial transformation. This formalism supports modular, scalable analysis of quantum information-driven spacetimes.

